dataIdInfo.idAbs:
Building additions contains additions to building structures that would not be captured as part of the actual building structure. The original data capture of the data in this layer was completed in 2013 using stereo models from the 2009 Virginia State imagery. Subsequent to that an update capture was completed in 2022 using stereo models from the 2017 Virginia State imagery. The most recent planimetric update was completed in 2024 using orthoimagery from the 2023 and 2022 Eagleview Orthophotos. The data in this layer includes decks, patios, pools, and aprons (patios for commercial buildings).

Contact: Fairfax County Department of Information Technology GIS Division

Data Accessibility: Publicly available

Update frequency: As Needed

Last Revision Date: 3/1/2024

Creation date: 1/1/2013

Layer name: GISMGR.BUILDING_ADDITIONS
dataIdInfo.idPurp: The primary purpose of this layer is to identify and depict the building additions and assign attributes to them (pool, deck, patio, apron). Another purpose of this layer is to identify impervious surfaces.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Fairfax County, Virginia;Fairfax County Department of Information Technology GIS Division, Avineon Inc. and Timmons Group (2017 & 2023 Updates), Geodecisions and Plangraphics, Inc (2009 Updates)
